tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE courses (
    course_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    course_name TEXT,
    course_description TEXT,
    instructor_name TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE enrollments (
    enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    course_id INT,
    student_id INT,
    enrollment_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (course_id) REFERENCES course_materials(course_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (student_id) REFERENCES students(student_id)
);

CREATE TABLE course_materials (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  title TEXT,
  content TEXT,
  author TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE students (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  first_name TEXT,
  last_name TEXT,
  email TEXT,
  enrollment_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE enrolled_courses (
  student_id INT,
  course_id INT,
  enrollment_date DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY (student_id) REFERENCES students(id),
  FOREIGN KEY (course_id) REFERENCES course_materials(id)
)

CREATE TABLE courses (
  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  title TEXT,
  description TEXT,
  instructor TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE courses (course_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 course_name TEXT,
 instructor TEXT)

CREATE TABLE course_materials (material_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 course_id INT,
 material_type TEXT,
 material_url TEXT)

CREATE TABLE students (student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 student_name TEXT,
 course_id INT)

CREATE TABLE enrollments (enrollment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 student_id INT,
 course_id INT,
 enrollment_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE assessments (assessment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
 course_id INT,
 student_id INT,
 grade FLOAT)
